msgid ""
"The goal of this section is to standardize the terms used within the media "
"userspace API documentation. This is Work In Progress."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:15
msgid "Bridge Driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:17
msgid ""
"A :term:`Device Driver` that implements the main logic to talk with media "
"hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:19
msgid "CEC API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:21
msgid "**Consumer Electronics Control API**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:23
msgid "An API designed to receive and transmit data via an HDMI CEC interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:26
msgid "See :ref:`cec`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:27
msgid "Data Unit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:30
msgid ""
"Unit of data transported by a bus. On parallel buses, the data unit consists "
"of one or more related samples while on serial buses the data unit is "
"logical. If the data unit is image data, it may also be called a pixel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:34
msgid "Device Driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:36
msgid ""
"Part of the Linux Kernel that implements support for a hardware component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:38
msgid "Device Node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:40
msgid ""
"A character device node in the file system used to control and transfer data "
"in and out of a Kernel driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:42
msgid "Digital TV API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:44
msgid "**Previously known as DVB API**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:46
msgid ""
"An API designed to control a subset of the :term:`Media Hardware` that "
"implements digital TV (e. g. DVB, ATSC, ISDB, etc)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:49
msgid "See :ref:`dvbapi`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:50
msgid "DSP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:52
msgid "**Digital Signal Processor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:54
msgid ""
"A specialized :term:`Microprocessor`, with its architecture optimized for "
"the operational needs of digital signal processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:56
msgid "FPGA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:58
msgid "**Field-programmable Gate Array**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:60
msgid ""
"An :term:`IC` circuit designed to be configured by a customer or a designer "
"after manufacturing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:63
msgid "See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Field-programmable_gate_array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:64
msgid "Hardware Component"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:66
msgid ""
"A subset of the :term:`Media Hardware`. For example an :term:`I²C` or :term:"
"`SPI` device, or an :term:`IP Block` inside an :term:`SoC` or :term:`FPGA`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:69
msgid "Hardware Peripheral"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:71
msgid ""
"A group of :term:`hardware components <Hardware Component>` that together "
"make a larger user-facing functional peripheral. For instance, the :term:"
"`SoC` :term:`ISP` :term:`IP Block` and the external camera sensors together "
"make a camera hardware peripheral."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:77
msgid "Also known as :term:`Peripheral`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:78
msgid "I²C"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:80
msgid "**Inter-Integrated Circuit**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:82
msgid ""
"A  multi-master, multi-slave, packet switched, single-ended, serial computer "
"bus used to control some hardware components like sub-device hardware "
"components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:86
msgid "See http://www.nxp.com/docs/en/user-guide/UM10204.pdf."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:87
msgid "IC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:89
msgid "**Integrated circuit**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:91
msgid ""
"A set of electronic circuits on one small flat piece of semiconductor "
"material, normally silicon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:94
msgid "Also known as chip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:95
msgid "IP Block"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:97
msgid "**Intellectual property core**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:99
msgid ""
"In electronic design a semiconductor intellectual property core, is a "
"reusable unit of logic, cell, or integrated circuit layout design that is "
"the intellectual property of one party. IP Blocks may be licensed to another "
"party or can be owned and used by a single party alone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:105
msgid ""
"See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semiconductor_intellectual_property_core)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:106
msgid "ISP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:108
msgid "**Image Signal Processor**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/glossary.rst:110
msgid ""
"A specialized processor that implements a set of algorithms for processing "
"image data. ISPs may implement algorithms for lens shading correction, "
"demosaicing, scaling and pixel format conversion as well as produce "
"statistics for the use of the control algorithms (e.g. automatic exposure, "
"white balance and focus)."
msgstr ""

